  "content": "ID: T1567.001\nTitle: Exfiltration Over Web Service:Exfiltration to Code Repository\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1567/001\nAdversaries may exfiltrate data to a code repository rather than over their primary command and control channel. Code repositories are often accessible via an API (ex: https://api.github.com). Access to these APIs are often over HTTPS, which gives the adversary an additional level of protection. Exfiltration to a code repository can also provide a significant amount of cover to the adversary if it is a popular service already used by hosts within the network.",
  "category": "Article",
  "source": "Local Storage",
